replies.body:
Random question I'm hoping IronStylus will pick up on if he gets a moment;

There's been a lot of discussion about the direction of Taric as a champion in his art, narrative and abilities etc. including his 'outrageous' reputation and the fact that the community sometimes see him as a well loved joke.

With regards to his visual upgrade, what sort of thought has been out into the update of his Armour of the Fifth Age skin? Is there a concerted direction in mind of retaining its humorous aspects, or is that not something you've been really concerned with preserving given that it's a skin and not central to the character?
